The paper deals with incentive compatibility and stability issues in matching mechanisms, which are topics that fall under game theory (cs.GT) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of envy-graphs in the algorithm suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the study of graph theory and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also involves the computation of stable matchings, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and multi-agent systems (cs.MA).
